notes: The Runway Incursion database contains records of events involving the incorrect presence of an aircraft, vehicle or person on the protected area of a surface designated for the landing and take off of aircraft.  Runway incursion events are reported by the respective air traffic control tower.  The data reflect the ICAO definition of a runway incursion as well as the related severity categories.  The runway incursion database is maintained by the FAA Office of Runway Safety.
